            <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:1;8:16" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/Filip/Desktop/-Screenshots-best-practices/Topics/Ho%20to%20create%20a%20perfect%20screenshot/t_how%20to_4_editing.dita">✅ Crop screenshots to show the relevant information. Don't include the full
                window if you just want to show a single button or menu item. Cropping helps the
                reader focus on the information that you want to convey in the screenshot, and it
                can help future-proof the screenshot if other parts of the UI change.<simpletable class="- topic/simpletable " frame="none" id="simpletable_gm5_3bv_ktb" relcolwidth="1* 1*" xtrc="simpletable:1;12:83" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/Filip/Desktop/-Screenshots-best-practices/Topics/Ho%20to%20create%20a%20perfect%20screenshot/t_how%20to_4_editing.dita">
